### Gun Violence in Virginia

In an average year, 992 people die by guns in Virginia. With a rate of 11.4 deaths per 100,000 people, Virginia has the 34th-highest rate of gun deaths in the United States. (Data provided by EveryStat for Gun Safty), read the full article here: Every-State-Fact-Sheet-2.0-042720-Virginia.pdf [everytownresearch.org](www.everytownresearch.org)
:::


